File: src/compiler/js-native-context-specialization.cc
Symbol: JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSEqual/ReduceJSStrictEqual handling null/undefined folding to ObjectIsUndetectable (JSEqual case)
Excerpt: In ReduceJSEqual: when OneInputIs(Type::NullOrUndefined()) the code relaxes effects/controls and morphs node to simplified()->ObjectIsUndetectable() with single operand. It builds JSGraphAssembler paths to compare to Undefined/Null and then ObjectIsUndetectable on the counterpart.
Context: [js_typed_lowering, native_context_specialization, ObjectIsUndetectable, protector-dependency]
Explanation: This entry records where JSNativeContextSpecialization turns equality against null/undefined into ObjectIsUndetectable checks, which is the origin of protector dependency attachment later in lowering.
FileLine: "compiler/js-typed-lowering.cc:932-990"
explanation: Records ReduceJSEqual handling null/undefined -> ObjectIsUndetectable; important for tracing dependency attachment.
